    <tr>
        <td colspan="2">
          <h3><font size="4" face="Arial"><a name="agriculture"></a>Agriculture</font></h3>
          <p><font
        face="Arial">The </font><a
        href="http://www.ifap.org/develop/africainit.html"><font
        face="Arial">Office National de Développement Rural
        (ONDR)</font></a><font face="Arial"> organises farmers to
        put their harvests together, and work in common fields to
        produce a maximum harvest. </font><a
        href="http://www.ifap.org/develop/africainit.html"><font
        face="Arial">ONDR</font></a><font face="Arial"> also
        provides ploughs. They also help run public granaries.
        Using stars, and weather information, they offer
        suggestions on when farmers should begin planting their
        crops.</font></p>
        <p><a href="http://www.catholicrelief.org/"><font
        face="Arial">Catholic Relief Fund (SECADEV)</font></a><font
        face="Arial"> projects help villagers to take charge of
        meeting their needs by organising village groups toward
        market farming and vineyards. They also provide farmers
        with access to hoes and seeds.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial">The </font><a
        href="http://www.swisscoalition.ch/"><font face="Arial">Swiss
        Relief Agencies</font></a><font face="Arial"> help the
        farmers buy agricultural tools. They also give advice
        concerning public granaries.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial">US-AID has established the </font><a
        href="http://www.fews.org/"><font face="Arial">Famine
        Early Warning System (FEWS)</font></a><font face="Arial">
        to help with the early co-ordination of emergency relief
        aid in the case of famine. They have an office in
        N'Djaména.</font></p>
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
        <td colspan="2">&nbsp;</td>
