    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
        <td colspan="2">
          <h3><font size="4" face="Arial"><a name="health"></a>Health Issues</font></h3>
          <p><font size="3" face="Arial">For
          over five years, the Italian NGO Cooperazione
          Internationale (COOPI) is responsible for all the
          medical aid work and the management of the hospital in the Health
          District of Goz-Beïda.&nbsp; They run nine dispensaries in the
          District (Kerfi, Doroti, Koukou, Ade, Moudeina, Tiorro, Daguessa,
          Saraf-Bourgou et Tissi).&nbsp; In a region that suffers from almost
          complete isolation, their work is essential to the life of these
          villages.</font></p>
          <p><a
        href="http://www.catholicrelief.org/"><font face="Arial">Catholic
        Relief (SECADEV)</font></a><font face="Arial"> assists
        those living in rural areas to meet their development
        needs by establishing rural health centres. They opened a
        dispensary in Miltou and Bardangal (Dar Dadjo region),
        among others.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial">There is also a leprosy clinic in
        Kokaga in the Guéra.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial">The Abéché orphanage has helped
        the Assangori to build a health centre in Troane. Doctor
        Sutton of </font><a
        href="http://www.wec-int.org/chad/index.htm"><font
        size="3" face="Arial">WEC</font></a><font size="3"
        face="Arial"> has</font><font face="Arial"> set up a
        network of dispensaries in all the Adré Sub-prefecture,
        in cooperation with the Ministry of Health.</font></p>
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
        <td width="655" colspan="2">&nbsp;</td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
        <td colspan="2">
          <h3><font size="4" face="Arial"><a name="transportation"></a>Transportation</font></h3>
          <p><font size="3" face="Arial">The
          work accomplished in Chad by <a href="http://www.asf-fr.org">Aviation
          Without Borders (ASF)</a>&nbsp; exists in close association with the
          Italian NGO Cooperazione Internationale
          (COOPI),&nbsp; responsible for the medical aid work undertaken
          in the Health District of Goz-Beïda over the past five years in the
          Ouaddaï.&nbsp; In practical terms, <a href="http://www.asf-fr.org">ASF</a>
          provides practical support to the nine dispensaries located in the
          District through its aviation program. The actual flights are
          primarily evacuations of persons needing emergency assistance to the
          Goz-Beïda hospital, logistical assistance for vaccination campaigns
          or the quick delivery of medicine to the dispensaries.<br>
          The leaders of <a href="http://www.asf-fr.org">Aviation Without
          Borders (ASF)</a> are open to all geographical extension projects of
          the work of dispensaries located in distant villages.&nbsp; This may
          be accomplished with the framework of financing programs such as those
          prepared by European Development Funds (FED) of the European Union, in partnership with Health organisations. To learn
          more, please <a href="mailto:pilot@asf-fr.org">contact them directly</a>.</font></p>
          <p><font
        face="Arial">The World Bank/European Economic Community
        (EEC) has financed the improvement of the road between
        Guélengdeng and Sarh, a work which began in 1995. In
        addition, The EEC has financed the improvement of the
        road between Mongo and Eref.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial">In Bandaro, </font><a
        href="http://www.swisscoalition.ch/"><font face="Arial">Swiss
        Relief Agencies</font></a><font face="Arial"> buy donkeys
        for the farmers to facilitate their travel. Thus, they
        are able to more easily travel to the areas where there
        is a market to sell their harvest or a health centre.</font></p>
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
